info.summary: The Wind Energy Toolbox (or ```wetb```, pronounce as wee-tee-bee) is a collection of Python scripts that facilitate working with (potentially a lot) of HAWC2, HAWCStab2, FAST or other text input based simulation tools.  Note that this toolbox is very much a WIP (work in progress). For example, some of the functions in the [prepost](#prepost) module have a similar functions in [Hawc2io](wetb/hawc2/Hawc2io.py). These different implementations will be merged in due time.  Both Python2 and Python3 are supported
